dismissalText.commentary: Kumar Sangakkara c Ali b Jordan 112 (112b 12x4 2x6 169m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: gives himself room again, aiming over the off side this time but picks out cover. And Sangakkara gives a long salute to the crowd as he walks off, his last innings here more than likely. Didn't get the timing right on this occasion and clothed a cut straight to Moeen Ali on the edge of the circle

dismissalText.commentary: Tillakaratne Dilshan c Bopara b Tredwell 68 (105b 8x4 0x6 134m) SR: 64.76

dismissalComment.html: down the track, slaps it down the ground but doesn't get in and holes out to long-on! Straight to Bopara, so Dilshan's lovely innings come to an end and England make the breakthrough. Dilshan didn't get to the pitch and got a thick inside edge that flew straight to the fielder who took a simple catch, no mistake this time

but gone next ball! Woakes pitches it touch fuller and Jayawardene gets completely squared up as he aims to play to the leg side, the leading edge looping to mid-off. The ball appeared to stop in the surface, as well as straighten

goes to swing this away again and gets it off high on the bat straight to mid-off. Perera was trying to slap it straight down the ground I think but got no kind of reasonable connection and this time Alastair Cook made no mistake, getting down low by his right boot to take the catch

dismissalText.commentary: Joe Root b Lakmal 55 (76b 4x4 0x6 114m) SR: 72.36

dismissalComment.html: goes for the scoop, misses and bowled! Root going right across his stumps and misses with an attempted scoop, losing his middle stump, embarrassment back on the cards for England. Nice and full and straight from the bowler, and when they miss, you know the rest

dismissalText.commentary: Chris Woakes c & b Dilshan 41 (49b 4x4 0x6 65m) SR: 83.67

dismissalComment.html: forward press, pushed back in the air to the bowler and taken low down! A smart return catch, indecision from the batsman, neither tried to belt it nor carefully steer it and pays the penalty. Innocuous off stump delivery, Woakes just misjudged the stroke and tapped it back a foot from the floor, Dilshan down well for the save

headshotImage.caption: Suranga Lakmal, player page headshot cutout 2022
headshotImage.longCaption: Suranga Lakmal, player page headshot cutout 2022

dismissalComment.html: wider line and driven at, edged to the keeper! A tumbling catch but Sangakkara looks hurt. I think he's got the catch but Sangakkara went to ground and didn't celebrate. He's lost the ball but it's slid down his arms and stayed above ground so Bopara has to go and Sangakkara gets away with what should have been a straightforward take down to his right. I think he fell on the ball so was nursing a bang to his chest but whatever happened he claimed the catch. More on the stroke, it was a wild drive from Bopara without foot movement. The delivery left him a little and took a solid outside edge

oh what a beauty! Back of a length lifts on Morgan and he gloves it behind! Pretty much unplayable first up. Right on line sliding across the left-hander but the extra bounce saw Morgan trying to fend it off and he got a thin glove to the keeper. Perfect delivery and this time no drama with the catch

goes for the scoop, misses and bowled! Root going right across his stumps and misses with an attempted scoop, losing his middle stump, embarrassment back on the cards for England. Nice and full and straight from the bowler, and when they miss, you know the rest

decent length just outside off, it nibbles away a little, and takes a thin edge behind! A fourth for Lakmal what a performance from him today. Jordan pushing half-forward just outside off and getting a feather edge to the keeper who took the catch one-handed, blindfolded singing the sinhalese version of It's A Long Way To Tipperary

dismissalComment.html: his day gets no better! Shuffling across his crease, it's a short of a length delivery which angles into him and strikes him on the thigh pad. Umpire raises his finger quickly and Cook doesn't consider the review. His problems continue to mount. Replays show that it was giving leg stump a solid whack

oh, wonderful stuff from Senanayake who has done Taylor all ends up. It was the delivery going on with the arm, Taylor came the pitch and was probably looking for turn. Instead the ball slides past the edge into off stump

down the track again and up she goes, this has gone noewhere and taken by mid-on! A smart catch because that went a long way up but another chance for Dilshan to celebrate. Not the strike Tredwell was looking for, a top edge high into the sky and that's the ball game

commentTextItems.html: down the track again and up she goes, this has gone noewhere and taken by mid-on! A smart catch because that went a long way up but another chance for Dilshan to celebrate. Not the strike Tredwell was looking for, a top edge high into the sky and that's the ball game

commentPostTextItems.html: So the series is wrapped up with a game to play, that seventh and final one-dayer is back down at the Premadasa on Tuesday, another day-nighter, so 2.30pm local time and 9am GMT, see you then...

Presentation coming up shortly where the Man of the Match is probably going to be some chap named Kumar. Said Kumar is out on a lap of honour and now has to come and pick up his cheque. Safe to say, a popular choice. Russell Arnold simply hands over the microphone and Sangakkara can say goodbye to his local fans, looking like a definite retirement post-World Cup then...

Alastair Cook is back on the losing side once again: "A real tough day. For the first 20 odd overs we bowled really well. it didn't help me dropping Sanga, It was a real big catch to drop because we'd built up some good pressure. It was probably about a 260 wicket. Credit to Kumar, he made us pay today. My form is hard, you want to score runs. I want to lead from the top of the order and it's tough at the moment. We'll look out our side when we get to Colombo."

Angelo Mathews: "Brilliant game. It was a challenging wicket to bat on. Sangakkara was amazing and set the tone for the batsman to play at the end. The option is still open at the top of the order but Mahela's been batting well at No. 4. the last game we bowled pretty badly but today from ball one we were landing the ball in the right stop. We might try a few things now in Colombo but we'll have a chat to the selectors."

You can say England were troubled by a spinning wicket but it's actually been the seam of Suranga Lakmal that has ruined their chase with four wickets in the middle order, including that of Joe Root who was the only bright point for the visitors with a fluent half-century but found no support today. This has perhaps been England's weakest performance with the bat this series, being bowled out with so much time left in the innings. They will be doubly disappointed with this display coming so soon after their best showing for some time in the fifth ODI only two days ago.

Sri Lanka have put in an excellent performance in the field and were always in control of this second half and have won by 90 runs to clinch the series with a rubber still to play. Bar the first 10 overs of this match, Sri Lanka have been by far the better side today, Kumar Sangakkara made a wonderful century and in the end he's led his side to victory and takes the applause from all sides of the ground and leads his side off in his final ODI in Pallekele.

dismissalText.commentary: Seekkuge Prasanna c Morgan b Finn 20 (12b 1x4 2x6 11m) SR: 166.66

dismissalComment.html: another slog, mistimed again and this time caught. It was a slower ball that Prasanna tried to heave away again but he got a thick outside edge that only looped to point and Morgan made no mistake - Buttler's error not costing England too many

headshotImage.caption: Angelo Mathews, player page headshot cutout 2023
headshotImage.longCaption: Angelo Mathews, player page headshot cutout 2023

headshotImage.caption: Angelo Mathews, player page headshot cutout 2023
headshotImage.longCaption: Angelo Mathews, player page headshot cutout 2023

dismissalText.commentary: Angelo Mathews c †Buttler b Finn 1 (5b 0x4 0x6 7m) SR: 20

dismissalComment.html: length down the leg side, taken by Buttler and an immediate appeal and given out caught behind! Mathews walks off. He shuffled across his stumps a little and tried to leg glance this but got a tickle to Buttler who went straight up and Mathews walked straight off, a big wicket

dismissalText.commentary: Kumar Sangakkara c Ali b Jordan 112 (112b 12x4 2x6 169m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: gives himself room again, aiming over the off side this time but picks out cover. And Sangakkara gives a long salute to the crowd as he walks off, his last innings here more than likely. Didn't get the timing right on this occasion and clothed a cut straight to Moeen Ali on the edge of the circle

headshotImage.caption: Alastair Cook player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Alastair Cook player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Thisara Perera c Cook b Woakes 16 (10b 3x4 0x6 12m) SR: 160

dismissalComment.html: goes to swing this away again and gets it off high on the bat straight to mid-off. Perera was trying to slap it straight down the ground I think but got no kind of reasonable connection and this time Alastair Cook made no mistake, getting down low by his right boot to take the catch

headshotImage.caption: Dinesh Chandimal, player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Dinesh Chandimal, player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Dinesh Chandimal, player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Dinesh Chandimal, player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Dinesh Chandimal b Jordan 35 (31b 4x4 0x6 60m) SR: 112.9

dismissalComment.html: yorker length and aiming off side. Very full and very straight - amazing how simple the game can be sometimes. Chandimal misses leaning across having backed to leg and loses his off stump

headshotImage.caption: Alastair Cook player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Alastair Cook player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Alastair Cook player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Alastair Cook player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Alastair Cook lbw b Senanayake 1 (2b 0x4 0x6 1m) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: his day gets no better! Shuffling across his crease, it's a short of a length delivery which angles into him and strikes him on the thigh pad. Umpire raises his finger quickly and Cook doesn't consider the review. His problems continue to mount. Replays show that it was giving leg stump a solid whack

dismissalText.commentary: Moeen Ali c †Sangakkara b Dilshan 34 (32b 4x4 2x6 33m) SR: 106.25

dismissalComment.html: a crackerjack! A ripper from Dilshan. Gripped off a length, bounced and feathered Moeen's glove has he, perfectly understandably, came forward. Not much he could have done, really.

dismissalText.commentary: James Taylor b Senanayake 10 (12b 1x4 0x6 18m) SR: 83.33

dismissalComment.html: oh, wonderful stuff from Senanayake who has done Taylor all ends up. It was the delivery going on with the arm, Taylor came the pitch and was probably looking for turn. Instead the ball slides past the edge into off stump

headshotImage.caption: Suranga Lakmal, player page headshot cutout 2022
headshotImage.longCaption: Suranga Lakmal, player page headshot cutout 2022

dismissalText.commentary: Joe Root b Lakmal 55 (76b 4x4 0x6 114m) SR: 72.36

dismissalComment.html: goes for the scoop, misses and bowled! Root going right across his stumps and misses with an attempted scoop, losing his middle stump, embarrassment back on the cards for England. Nice and full and straight from the bowler, and when they miss, you know the rest

headshotImage.caption: Suranga Lakmal, player page headshot cutout 2022
headshotImage.longCaption: Suranga Lakmal, player page headshot cutout 2022

dismissalText.commentary: Ravi Bopara c †Sangakkara b Lakmal 13 (20b 2x4 0x6 28m) SR: 65

dismissalComment.html: wider line and driven at, edged to the keeper! A tumbling catch but Sangakkara looks hurt. I think he's got the catch but Sangakkara went to ground and didn't celebrate. He's lost the ball but it's slid down his arms and stayed above ground so Bopara has to go and Sangakkara gets away with what should have been a straightforward take down to his right. I think he fell on the ball so was nursing a bang to his chest but whatever happened he claimed the catch. More on the stroke, it was a wild drive from Bopara without foot movement. The delivery left him a little and took a solid outside edge

headshotImage.caption: Suranga Lakmal, player page headshot cutout 2022
headshotImage.longCaption: Suranga Lakmal, player page headshot cutout 2022

dismissalText.commentary: Eoin Morgan c †Sangakkara b Lakmal 0 (1b 0x4 0x6 1m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: oh what a beauty! Back of a length lifts on Morgan and he gloves it behind! Pretty much unplayable first up. Right on line sliding across the left-hander but the extra bounce saw Morgan trying to fend it off and he got a thin glove to the keeper. Perfect delivery and this time no drama with the catch

dismissalText.commentary: Jos Buttler run out (Thirimanne) 22 (26b 2x4 0x6 31m) SR: 84.61

dismissalComment.html: brilliant fielding! Buttler dropped the ball into the off side, he wanted the run but Root sent him back fairly quickly. Thirimanne swooped from cover and produced a direct hit almost with a back-handed throw as he still in a diving motion

dismissalText.commentary: Chris Woakes c & b Dilshan 41 (49b 4x4 0x6 65m) SR: 83.67

dismissalComment.html: forward press, pushed back in the air to the bowler and taken low down! A smart return catch, indecision from the batsman, neither tried to belt it nor carefully steer it and pays the penalty. Innocuous off stump delivery, Woakes just misjudged the stroke and tapped it back a foot from the floor, Dilshan down well for the save

headshotImage.caption: Suranga Lakmal, player page headshot cutout 2022
headshotImage.longCaption: Suranga Lakmal, player page headshot cutout 2022

dismissalText.commentary: Chris Jordan c †Sangakkara b Lakmal 4 (6b 1x4 0x6 7m) SR: 66.66

dismissalComment.html: decent length just outside off, it nibbles away a little, and takes a thin edge behind! A fourth for Lakmal what a performance from him today. Jordan pushing half-forward just outside off and getting a feather edge to the keeper who took the catch one-handed, blindfolded singing the sinhalese version of It's A Long Way To Tipperary

dismissalText.commentary: James Tredwell c Dilshan b Senanayake 19 (22b 0x4 1x6 24m) SR: 86.36

dismissalComment.html: down the track again and up she goes, this has gone noewhere and taken by mid-on! A smart catch because that went a long way up but another chance for Dilshan to celebrate. Not the strike Tredwell was looking for, a top edge high into the sky and that's the ball game

dismissalText.commentary: Steven Finn not out 1 (3b 0x4 0x6 8m) SR: 33.33
